      <summary>
        <versionCode>07</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2025-09-17</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Reported to House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2025-09-29T12:31:02Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;State Energy Accountability Act&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill directs each state that implements certain energy policies (e.g., policies that require solar or wind energy) to conduct, and make publicly available, a general evaluation of the effects that those policies have on the rates and reliability of the state's electric power grid, including information about meeting electricity demand during emergencies, periods of high demand, or extreme weather events.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
